    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        radiographs, photographs and dental plaster models of people who come to orthodontic
        treatment
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Both genders

          2. Age 18 to 60 years

          3. Case studies to understand orthodontic intraoral photographs of the upper and lower
             dental arches, and models of lateral skull radiography for orthodontic

          4. Cases with any facial biotype development.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Totally toothless people

          2. Partially toothless the posterior (include both molars and premolars).

          3. Dawn Syndrome,alzheimer , partial or bilateral facial palsy, autism, which manifest
             with bruxism

          4. Some other syndrome which alters the pattern of facial development as Pierre
             Robin,crouzon
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
